The paper discusses fault tolerance in digital system designs, which is a topic that falls under the category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the use of triple modular redundancy (TMR) and the design of a new fault-tolerant majority voter, which are topics that fall under the categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of nanoelectronics technology, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.EM). Finally, the paper discusses simulation results, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
